<statement>
<image width="33%"  pi:generated="problems/images/3e2f51dfcdab410f5f9b479bfd6b2a92.png" /><p>
Suppose a = 9 and A = 25 degrees. Calculate:</p>
<p>
b = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
c = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place.  Give angles in <em>degrees</em>
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>19.3</li><li>21.3</li><li>65.0</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p>For the length of the other leg,</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\tan{{\left({25}\right)}}}=\frac{{9}}{{b}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}=\frac{{9}}{{\tan{{\left({25}\right)}}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}\approx{19.300562284586}\approx{19.3}</m>.</p>
<p>For the third side</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={9}^{{2}}+{19.300562284586}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={81}+{372.51170450118}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={453.51170450118}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}=\sqrt{{{453.51170450118}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{21.295814248372}\approx{21.3}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{B}={180}^{\circ}-{90}^{\circ}-{25}^{\circ}\approx{65}^{\circ}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

